What are techniques for pull spliting that you would recomend for a mid-20s bard? Any tips on what to watch for/do when someone else is trying to split pull?
<br />

<br />
I ask because in shadeweavers thicket I was working with 5-7 Gor Taku bruisers and pulling them up the tunnel with my new Tambouine. Usually I only had 2-3 at the end of the tunnel waiting for me to pick up upon my return. I found this to be a very sucessful technique.
<br />

<br />
(I know I should be practicing charm/swarm kiting but I've been finding it hard to practice as my wife(28 Ranger) usually wants to play with me and I've found I need space.)
<br />

