			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Pull Spliting<a name="77440"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 11 05 10:53 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>To answer your question about &quot;speed pulling&quot; more thouroughly, yes there are a couple of ways to speed up the process without having to sit and lull every other mob in the world.
<br />

<br />
First, have your drum equipped (seems silly to say, but yes it's important) and sing selo's to give that fast run speed.
<br />

<br />
For &quot;easy&quot; splits try three mobs at a time, to start
<br />

<br />
Pull with Bellow or a thrown weapon, use range to give you that added buffer space and to help reduce the likelyhood of pulling ten by accident.
<br />

<br />
Have a &quot;target nearest NPC&quot; key set up, I use mine all the time, only drawback is it only works once the mob is withing 30 feet or so, very close range.
<br />

<br />
Mob one, snare with Selo's Consonant Chain, level 23 song
<br />

<br />
Pull back towards your group a bit more
<br />

<br />
Mob two, mez with Kellin's Lucid Lullabye, level 15 song
<br />

<br />
Mob three pull to group to kill, let the tank aggro.  When that mezzed mob breaks it will run after you, be ready to mez again and you'll have one waiting for when the first mob dies, groups really really like that.
<br />

<br />
Once you work out the range, you should be running away from the snared mob far enough that it won't keep chasing you, if it does then stop meleeing and mez both mobs, you don't get charm until late 20's or that would be the thing to do instead (more DPS is good).
<br />

<br />
Once you start doing three things at a time it will seem very hectic, the trick is to stay in control of what the mobs are doing, stop meleeing and sing mez only if you have to.  
<br />

<br />
Good luck
<br />
</span></td>
